layout.p:
Columns: 40;
                                                  ruled lines: 13;
                                                  written lines: 13; Uniform layout. Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.Visible pricking. Hair side and flesh side of membranes distinguishable. Three tagin on שעטנזגץ and ס, and one on בדהחיק. The letter ח arched sometimes, and occasionally בהםסרת at the end of a line. The letter ע flourished in the last word of the Megillah. No majuscular or minuscular letters. The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 6 lines. Ivory roller (150mm high). The first and part of the second membrane lined with green silk.
